<plot>Four characters live voluntarily confined for 24 hours surrounded with drugs, alcohol and endless games of dominoes. A cocaine plate is the clock that marks time. Each minute is counted by the lines of cocaine and levels in bottles of alcohol. This sit-in will be interrupted by a series of hallucinations in which these men try to protect their fears and the dark side of their minds. Dog's Hell is a glance into madness, the ego and the monsters of ones' conscience. View the worst violence from a gaming table.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?264830</url></doc>
